So yea here i am in the middle of the day, nevermind the fact that i'm supposed to be in ap english hah! school, what a laugh... anywho,wilma has left me without electrucity for almost two weeks now but i fared better than alot of people. I hope all you uys are doing good and ive missed you so much! those days without communication to my vital people were hell i tell...HELL!!! its amazing just how important some people become, without them ure well numb (thanks for that term, it really is the best one smoochie lol) 
     Im so looking forward to friday and saturday. On friday a whole night with chris (dont be dorkalicious gen) and on saturday the day with gen and tina. It's going to be awesome my luvs!!! I hope turtle can come along, vane would but she is now tied down to smoothies and such. I have to admit...gen+car= my possible death BUT i should live on the edge after all i guess lol. 
     Recent events have made me realize that yet another one of my so called friends is lost forever. i used to think we were friends eventhough we had barely talked anymore but i was obviously oh so wrong. In the end i guess you always know who it is you can count on. i have done so much i regret and am sorry for, however, if any of the people i no longer talk to came to me i would gladly help them because i still love them. Yea..even you. 


anyways...enough rambling and ill probably update in another ten years.

oh and gen no one cares about ure frustrations with tito and christian..pfft we both kno u are waaaay worst <3

Alot has happened, and it was all very good. Then, of course, my life takes the course that, apparently, it's meant to take. At the risk of sounding suicidal and emo-like, it all goes to crap. I'm not really sure what'll go down next. Maybe nothing will, but all i know is that i'm not going to be the one to turn around and walk away. For once, and thanks to alot of great advice, i'm not going to run away. 
  The catch, however, is that i'm not really sure if whether im sticking around matters or not. With time, i guess, everything will fall into place and we'll just see what happens. Enough about this though...
  Today i'll be hanging out with Gen and Tina. I'm sure i'll have a blast, i love those two. They really do make things better for me.:D 
  I'm missing turtle so badly, he has to stop enjoying summer and stay bored with me for at least one weekend! 

p.s. Steven, sorry about not going to ur party, i hope u had a great time. 
MUAH !!

First off, i hope everyone had a great Father's Day..ok now, i had a great weekend. I hung out with alot of friends who are fast becoming the most special people to me, and i also hung out with those who already are the most special. The Novelties performance on friday was in one word amazing. Now on to Saturday..wow.I had a great time. I wish i wasn't so shy and retarded. It's like I overthink everything to the point that by the time i work up the guts to do it its either too late or so much less than i expected. I'll work on that though. Anywhoo..we all  saw batman Begins..some for the 22456454th time (chris), it was a good movie. I could barely concentrate the whole time,though,and it had nothing to do with Chris's non stop comments. lol.All in all, everything was awesome and i hope we all hang out again some time soon.

So yea ten minutes too late although i told him in person long ago...HAPPY BIRTHDAY LOVE!!!!!!! 
(aka Alberto)

Hope this year goes awesome and that everything you wish for and more comes true..thanks for being such an amazing best friend..love ya lots ;)

Wow, last night was so fun! I was so glad to have all of the people that went there. I mean i just genuinely enjoyed the whole night, that hasn't happened in a while, so it was great. I met Natalie which was great, i hope she had fun and wasn't too creeped out by us. I'm really happy that i saw alberto and vanessa totally fitting in and hanging with everyone. Chris kept ranking on me, but all is good because ha ha boy is he going to regret it lol 9and all of hialeah is all mine!!). I love the relationship Genesis and Tito have, it's so comfortable..random comment but i had to mention it. The movie was great, thanks for forcing me to see it.



oh and by the way Tina, you aren't supposed text ppl in movies..it goes against the whole fat lady singing warning.

i dont kno about my perfect date, specifically, but i'd love it if it includes the beach at night and the stars and sky and stuff..corrny i kno, but w/e...
2. What's one thing you want to achieve before you die? i want to mean something to someone, i basically want to be someone's one and only

Okay, this is what happens now:
1. Leave me a comment saying, "Interview me."
2. I will respond by asking you five questions. I get to pick the questions.
3. You will update your LJ with the answers to the questions and leave the answers as comments on my LJ.
4. You will include this explanation and an offer to interview someone else in the same post.
5. When others comment asking to be interviewed, you will ask them five questions.

Ugh! I have the cold from hell! I don't think I've felt so sick since....a long time. As it turns out, apparently, in order to join the disgust that is Mater Academy there's an effing waiting list! WTF?!?! Needless to say that the list is so long my skank name will get nowhere near the top by the time the new school year starts, therefore I'm stuck at Hialeah High. Not that it's a bad thing since I have alot to look forward to next year. These past few days have been umm..interesting..but w/e, i'm not going to comment on why. I think i might quit my "job," if you can call it that. It's a pointless waste of my time.

well, it was a busy night at the place where all the bums in the world decide to hang out at and enslave me until effing midnight. i mean really people why the hell would you spend your sunday night at chuck e. cheese if you're over the age of..oh i dont know..12!!! anyhow, iv'e decided to let someone who i cared about go. it's about time i moved on and realized that in the words of my true love alberto.."life's a bitch" and of course the oh so true.."fuck it." i only live once and spending that time pondering what could've and should've been will get me nowhere when there is nothing.  


ps..the time on this crap is so behind its funny

Well, i think this is my actual first entry..this time i wasnt forced.Alot has been going on and changing. Friends, family, school, work, seventeen..maybe a little too much for me to handle. It's like im being pulled in so many different directions. I really hope in the end i can be everywhere and do everything im expected to do because i simply cant let everything i have go.. not again and not right now.

ps. thank you all for being so amazing to me on my birthday..it meant more than i can say...i love you guys

It's been a weird couple of days. A lot of different things have happened that maybe shouldn't of. All in all, though, life's going good. I mean other than the fact that alot of people aren't what they seemed to be and aren't as there for me as i hoped they would be, it's all good. I've met alot of new ppl, they're great and we have alot more in common than i would've of ever thought. I'm confused though, about alot of things, and i think from this journal you'll notice it.

Well, this is my first entry and the truth is I'm doing it as a result of peer pressure. I'm not sure if i'll do it regularly because...well...im not really the teel the world about all that happens kind of person. specially since not much usually happens. anyways, this week has ben interesting. As you all know, it was spirit week at school and it was really fun. I only dressed for Hawaiin day but seeing Jorge dress up as something there (still don't kno what) for superhero day was effing hilarious. I also figured out alot of crap this week about alot of people even some of my friends. Well, eventually i'll get better at this but for now screw u all if u think this sucks.
